---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import PageHero from '../../components/PageHero.astro';
import ImageText from '../../components/ImageText.astro';
import BookingCTA from '../../components/BookingCTA.astro';
---
<Layout
	title="People with Neurological Conditions"
	description="Specialist neurological rehabilitation for MS, stroke, Parkinson's, cerebral palsy and other pathologies."
>
	<PageHero
		title="People with Neurological Conditions"
		breadcrumb="People with Neurological Conditions"
	/>

	<ImageText
		image="/neuro-rehab.jpg"
		imageAlt="Neurological rehabilitation at Balance Physio"
	>
		<p>Living with a neurological condition affects movement, balance, coordination, strength and independence in ways that reach into every area of daily life. The right rehabilitation, delivered consistently by the right people, makes a profound difference. At Balance, our specialist team supports people living with MS, stroke, Parkinson's, cerebral palsy and a wide range of other neurological pathologies.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<ImageText
		reverse
		altBg
		image="/who-we-help/neuro-conditions-2.jpg"
		imageAlt="Anti-gravity treadmill rehabilitation"
	>
		<p>Meaningful progress happens outside the treatment room, through consistent, active engagement with your programme. Our gym, movement studios and hydrotherapy facilities provide the environment for that daily work, and our anti-gravity treadmill enables safe, effective gait rehabilitation that rebuilds neural pathways and restores function in ways conventional therapy cannot always achieve.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<ImageText
		image="/vojta.jpg"
		imageAlt="Vojta therapy at Balance Physio"
	>
		<p>Vojta therapy is a specialist neurophysiological approach that activates the body's innate movement patterns and is a key part of our offer. It reflects the depth of expertise within our team and is one of the more specialised therapies available in London.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<ImageText
		reverse
		altBg
		image="/psychological-wellness.jpg"
		imageAlt="Psychological wellbeing support"
	>
		<p>We also understand that neurological rehabilitation is emotionally demanding. Our psychological wellbeing support sits alongside physical rehabilitation, ensuring the whole person is cared for throughout what is often a long and complex journey.</p>
		<p>At Balance, we are committed to helping you restore function, independence and energy for life.</p>
	</ImageText>

	<BookingCTA />
</Layout>
